1
00:00:09,379 --> 00:00:10,429
Hello, Mia.

2
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:32,350
So how have you been?

3
00:00:34,175 --> 00:00:35,075
Quiet.

4
00:00:35,725 --> 00:00:37,425
I hadn't heard from you.

5
00:00:38,315 --> 00:00:39,580
Did you get my message?

6
00:00:39,748 --> 00:00:41,598
Yes.
Thanks for your call.

7
00:00:42,824 --> 00:00:45,185
- And how are you feeling?
- How do I look?

8
00:00:45,310 --> 00:00:48,965
That's a lawyer technique, right...
answer a question with a question?

9
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:56,319
Well, I thought I'd hit bottom

10
00:00:56,444 --> 00:00:59,236
at the end of the last session,

11
00:00:59,361 --> 00:01:03,057
but it went downhill from there.

12
00:01:04,016 --> 00:01:06,232
I did figure something out, though.

13
00:01:07,038 --> 00:01:08,588
I'm stopping therapy.

14
00:01:31,837 --> 00:01:33,588
I appreciate what you've done.

15
00:01:33,713 --> 00:01:35,869
I know I'm a tough case.

16
00:01:36,087 --> 00:01:37,857
But if every time
you go to the doctor,

17
00:01:37,982 --> 00:01:41,132
you end up feeling worse,
then it's time to move on.

18
00:01:42,338 --> 00:01:46,095
And I could have called, but I wanted
to come in and say goodbye

19
00:01:47,459 --> 00:01:48,970
and wrap things up.

20
00:01:51,946 --> 00:01:53,096
I understand.

21
00:01:57,806 --> 00:01:59,869
You're not going to
try to convince me to stay?

22
00:02:01,136 --> 00:02:02,997
Is that what you'd like me to do?

23
00:02:03,165 --> 00:02:06,667
I just assumed you'd be all over me...
"therapy this, therapy that."

24
00:02:06,865 --> 00:02:09,302
You want me to hard-sell you

25
00:02:09,427 --> 00:02:12,298
like a guy selling you
a vegetable peeler on the street?

26
00:02:12,423 --> 00:02:13,548
Jeez, Paul,

27
00:02:15,526 --> 00:02:17,922
don't I get to be
the angry one here?

28
00:02:18,047 --> 00:02:21,497
You mad because I want to
leave or has something happened?

29
00:02:21,808 --> 00:02:24,185
You look like you want
to take your ball and go home.

30
00:02:24,841 --> 00:02:26,291
Maybe you're right.

31
00:02:27,655 --> 00:02:30,066
If therapy hasn't helped,

32
00:02:30,191 --> 00:02:33,395
the last thing I want to do
is keep you here, make you feel worse.

33
00:02:33,520 --> 00:02:36,270
That's what happened
after the last session.

34
00:02:41,875 --> 00:02:44,265
I felt like shit.

35
00:02:47,218 --> 00:02:51,044
And I went home and I called my dad,

36
00:02:51,169 --> 00:02:54,548
thinking that I should get
to the bottom of everything.

37
00:02:55,153 --> 00:02:58,358
He came over
and I started asking questions

38
00:02:58,595 --> 00:03:01,795
about my childhood,
all the things we'd talked about.

39
00:03:05,438 --> 00:03:06,988
He turned it on me...

40
00:03:08,724 --> 00:03:12,654
why was I creating problems,
bringing up ancient history?

41
00:03:13,517 --> 00:03:16,375
Maybe he felt threatened.

42
00:03:16,613 --> 00:03:20,498
Especially when I asked him
if it was his idea to sell the piano.

43
00:03:20,917 --> 00:03:22,076
He lost it...

44
00:03:22,343 --> 00:03:25,441
I shouldn't blame him;
I should be grateful;

45
00:03:25,789 --> 00:03:28,792
I wouldn't be alive without him;

46
00:03:29,824 --> 00:03:32,134
that I was impossible
from the day I was born,

47
00:03:32,259 --> 00:03:34,588
and maybe that's why
my mother went nuts.

48
00:03:35,077 --> 00:03:38,229
So it was all your fault.

49
00:03:38,354 --> 00:03:39,944
Yeah and he went on...

50
00:03:40,069 --> 00:03:42,969
it's no surprise
that I can't find a man;

51
00:03:43,094 --> 00:03:44,519
who would want

52
00:03:46,223 --> 00:03:47,726
a woman like me?

53
00:03:48,721 --> 00:03:51,515
And then he walked out,

54
00:03:51,640 --> 00:03:54,575
saying that he didn't want
to talk to me again.

55
00:03:56,871 --> 00:04:00,250
So therapy isn't the only
reason you had a bad week.

56
00:04:01,170 --> 00:04:05,105
I never would have confronted
him if I hadn't been talking to you.

57
00:04:06,461 --> 00:04:09,273
So thanks to all of this, I have...

58
00:04:09,398 --> 00:04:11,000
lost my father.

59
00:04:11,391 --> 00:04:13,356
You haven't lost your father.

60
00:04:14,387 --> 00:04:16,693
He's still in your life,

61
00:04:16,818 --> 00:04:20,661
but you did lose the father
that you thought you had.

62
00:04:21,371 --> 00:04:24,371
He didn't refute
your mother's version of events.

63
00:04:24,890 --> 00:04:27,275
He just chose not to answer.

64
00:04:28,587 --> 00:04:32,019
And that confirms a lot of the things
that we've been talking about in here.

65
00:04:32,144 --> 00:04:33,647
Okay, Paul, I get it.

66
00:04:34,962 --> 00:04:36,763
I didn't have the perfect dad.

67
00:04:36,888 --> 00:04:39,153
You're right and I'm wrong.
Is that what you want?

68
00:04:39,566 --> 00:04:43,226
So put that in today's session notes,
which I hope you keep now...

69
00:04:43,351 --> 00:04:46,604
"successfully shattered patient m's

70
00:04:46,729 --> 00:04:49,688
"romanticized image
of her narcissistic father."

71
00:04:49,813 --> 00:04:51,373
Actually what I would write is

72
00:04:51,542 --> 00:04:54,212
"Mia, born to a depressed mother,

73
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:59,870
"idealizes her father
so as not to feel completely alone.

74
00:04:59,995 --> 00:05:03,119
"And this week,
after finally confronting him,

75
00:05:04,516 --> 00:05:07,923
"she can see her dad
for who he really is."

76
00:05:11,150 --> 00:05:12,500
It is shattering,

77
00:05:14,367 --> 00:05:17,816
but if you can now move beyond
that connection to your father

78
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:19,869
it may open the possibility

79
00:05:20,674 --> 00:05:22,542
of finding love elsewhere.

80
00:05:26,012 --> 00:05:28,808
You mean, if I stay in therapy.

81
00:05:28,975 --> 00:05:30,225
That's one way.

82
00:05:30,544 --> 00:05:32,096
It's certainly not the only way.

83
00:05:32,221 --> 00:05:34,389
Good, because I really am done.

84
00:05:36,219 --> 00:05:38,419
In fact, maybe I should get going.

85
00:05:39,169 --> 00:05:40,619
You can, of course.

86
00:05:41,231 --> 00:05:45,091
But since you're here,
maybe we can at least work on...

87
00:05:45,216 --> 00:05:46,216
closure.

88
00:05:46,639 --> 00:05:48,799
I know you were unhappy
about the last time

89
00:05:48,924 --> 00:05:50,631
that we ended therapy.

90
00:05:51,219 --> 00:05:53,669
I'd like to do
a better job this time.

91
00:05:54,596 --> 00:05:56,063
How long does that take?

92
00:05:56,232 --> 00:05:57,882
Well, that's up to you.

93
00:05:58,950 --> 00:06:02,954
If this is your last session,
we'll use the time that's left.

94
00:06:03,357 --> 00:06:07,158
And I'll be honest, you be honest.

95
00:06:07,576 --> 00:06:08,575
How's that?

96
00:06:08,845 --> 00:06:10,439
Okay, last session.

97
00:06:15,829 --> 00:06:16,834
What do we do?

98
00:06:17,003 --> 00:06:19,440
You haven't told me what
happened after your father left.

99
00:06:19,565 --> 00:06:21,096
That's how we do closure?

100
00:06:21,221 --> 00:06:23,590
Couldn't we just burn
some sage or something?

101
00:06:26,562 --> 00:06:28,562
I enjoy your humor a lot, Mia.

102
00:06:30,526 --> 00:06:32,926
But sometimes I feel
it's a way of...

103
00:06:33,240 --> 00:06:34,790
It's a way of hiding.

104
00:06:45,196 --> 00:06:46,674
After dad left,

105
00:06:47,740 --> 00:06:50,674
I pretty much stayed home all week

106
00:06:52,901 --> 00:06:53,901
in bed.

107
00:06:57,759 --> 00:07:00,833
And I know that sounds bad,
but I'm here now,

108
00:07:00,958 --> 00:07:02,860
so I got through it.

109
00:07:03,525 --> 00:07:05,525
Did you get out of bed at all?

110
00:07:07,737 --> 00:07:11,188
Bathroom trips, kitchen trips.

111
00:07:11,313 --> 00:07:13,265
I answered the door for deliveries.

112
00:07:13,888 --> 00:07:15,434
Did you talk to anybody?

113
00:07:16,323 --> 00:07:17,939
My trusty assistant Henry,

114
00:07:18,064 --> 00:07:20,397
who threatened to come over
and cook for me.

115
00:07:20,730 --> 00:07:23,067
- You didn't want to call me?
- What would I have said...

116
00:07:23,236 --> 00:07:25,986
"I'm under the covers 'cause
I'm afraid of the living room"?

117
00:07:26,154 --> 00:07:29,120
If that's how you felt, then yes.

118
00:07:32,917 --> 00:07:35,120
Have you been feeling
a little hopeless?

119
00:07:36,673 --> 00:07:38,970
I'm not suicidal, Paul, don't worry.

120
00:07:39,095 --> 00:07:40,605
I am pretty tough.

121
00:07:41,169 --> 00:07:45,173
Does being tough mean you have to
suffer through things like this alone?

122
00:07:45,354 --> 00:07:47,504
I just felt like the bed was safe

123
00:07:49,051 --> 00:07:50,501
and the living room

124
00:07:51,353 --> 00:07:53,667
was scary.

125
00:07:54,060 --> 00:07:55,503
So you took to bed

126
00:07:57,190 --> 00:07:58,740
like your mother did.

127
00:08:00,298 --> 00:08:01,805
She had post-partum.

128
00:08:01,972 --> 00:08:04,888
What's my excuse... post-non-partum?

129
00:08:05,589 --> 00:08:08,237
I wouldn't belittle what
you've been through, Mia.

130
00:08:08,405 --> 00:08:09,943
You wanted a child.

131
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:12,508
You thought you were having one.

132
00:08:12,633 --> 00:08:14,233
That's a painful loss.

133
00:08:17,817 --> 00:08:20,567
And on top of that,
when you were vulnerable

134
00:08:20,855 --> 00:08:22,920
and need your father the most,

135
00:08:24,484 --> 00:08:26,184
he wasn't there for you,

136
00:08:28,257 --> 00:08:30,759
maybe the same way
he wasn't there for your mother

137
00:08:31,236 --> 00:08:33,386
when she couldn't get out of bed.

138
00:08:40,363 --> 00:08:44,256
This is exactly why
I'm done with therapy.

139
00:08:44,835 --> 00:08:46,835
Every time we talk, I feel like

140
00:08:46,960 --> 00:08:50,210
I need to see a therapist
just to get through the day.

141
00:08:50,880 --> 00:08:52,300
Okay, I hear you.

142
00:08:52,425 --> 00:08:55,325
- No more dad. No more mom.
- Is this how closure works?

143
00:08:55,493 --> 00:08:57,647
You remind me
of my miserable family life,

144
00:08:57,772 --> 00:09:00,581
and then my love life, and then what?
Global warming?

145
00:09:05,394 --> 00:09:07,421
So what would you
like to talk about?

146
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:09,989
I was thinking about
getting a parrot

147
00:09:11,349 --> 00:09:12,299
as a pet,

148
00:09:13,268 --> 00:09:15,718
instead of a boyfriend
or a therapist.

149
00:09:16,843 --> 00:09:18,343
I could name it paul

150
00:09:19,219 --> 00:09:21,769
and I could teach it
to say things like,

151
00:09:22,089 --> 00:09:23,729
"what would you like to talk about?"

152
00:09:23,897 --> 00:09:26,147
Or "is it me or is it your father?"

153
00:09:26,825 --> 00:09:29,722
But then I found out
that parrots live for about 80 years.

154
00:09:29,847 --> 00:09:32,321
And I don't think I could
stand anybody for that long.

155
00:09:32,701 --> 00:09:35,087
So you want to go,
but you also want to keep me around,

156
00:09:35,212 --> 00:09:37,662
or at least you want
to keep my voice.

157
00:09:38,013 --> 00:09:39,359
Look, paul,

158
00:09:39,997 --> 00:09:41,266
I like you

159
00:09:42,694 --> 00:09:44,344
I like you as a person.

160
00:09:45,612 --> 00:09:47,377
I mean, that's pretty obvious.

161
00:09:48,770 --> 00:09:50,220
If we were friends,

162
00:09:51,092 --> 00:09:53,130
that would be great.

163
00:09:57,186 --> 00:09:58,386
But we're not.

164
00:09:58,707 --> 00:10:01,369
And I don't imagine you're
going to become my friend.

165
00:10:01,494 --> 00:10:03,018
That's against the rules.

166
00:10:04,444 --> 00:10:07,554
Unless, of course,
my name were laura.

167
00:10:07,941 --> 00:10:10,901
- You're still angry about that.
- Maybe I'm just an angry person

168
00:10:11,069 --> 00:10:13,177
and I should just accept
myself for who I am.

169
00:10:13,302 --> 00:10:16,657
- No, you're specifically angry at me.
- No, I said I like you.

170
00:10:16,913 --> 00:10:19,094
And you want me as a friend
but not as a therapist.

171
00:10:19,219 --> 00:10:21,119
You want what I can't give you.

172
00:10:21,288 --> 00:10:22,314
What else is new?

173
00:10:22,439 --> 00:10:24,998
Maybe the question isn't
why you're leaving, mia,

174
00:10:25,166 --> 00:10:26,959
but why you came back
in the first place.

175
00:10:27,721 --> 00:10:31,171
You clearly knew that I was
being sued for malpractice. And

176
00:10:31,339 --> 00:10:33,986
you believed that I had
failed you 20 years ago.

177
00:10:34,111 --> 00:10:36,343
Think about it.
What kind of choice was that?

178
00:10:36,511 --> 00:10:38,411
It wasn't a really good one.

179
00:10:39,039 --> 00:10:40,739
Or maybe it was perfect,

180
00:10:41,776 --> 00:10:44,309
if you were trying to choose
a therapist in the same way that

181
00:10:44,477 --> 00:10:47,639
you choose the men in your life

182
00:10:48,759 --> 00:10:51,079
look for someone who's
likely to let you down,

183
00:10:51,204 --> 00:10:53,190
do everything you can
to drive him away,

184
00:10:53,315 --> 00:10:55,612
and when he fails you,
which he must inevitably,

185
00:10:56,879 --> 00:10:59,029
then you get to rage against him.

186
00:11:03,698 --> 00:11:04,798
Nicely done.

187
00:11:05,598 --> 00:11:08,961
You've even doubled back to dad,
without having to mention him.

188
00:11:09,086 --> 00:11:11,378
Look, mia,
of course you're free to leave

189
00:11:11,689 --> 00:11:12,589
therapy,

190
00:11:13,272 --> 00:11:15,872
but my guess is,
until you untangle those

191
00:11:17,144 --> 00:11:18,344
crossed wires,

192
00:11:18,768 --> 00:11:22,077
the next man, and the one after that,
and the one after that

193
00:11:22,202 --> 00:11:23,890
they're going to disappoint you too.

194
00:11:25,112 --> 00:11:26,912
That's my lifelong pattern

195
00:11:28,651 --> 00:11:30,001
because I've been

196
00:11:31,829 --> 00:11:33,734
too attached to bad dad?

197
00:11:37,667 --> 00:11:40,267
Why didn't you tell
me this 20 years ago?

198
00:11:40,517 --> 00:11:43,368
- I mean, what the fuck?
- Are you saying it's my fault?

199
00:11:43,536 --> 00:11:46,132
Maybe I would have had a decent
life if I had known that.

200
00:11:46,257 --> 00:11:47,788
It's a little late now.

201
00:11:47,913 --> 00:11:50,693
Would you have even heard me
if I'd said it that back then?

202
00:11:50,818 --> 00:11:52,284
So you waited?

203
00:11:53,702 --> 00:11:56,840
And while you waited,
I hit perimenopause? Great.

204
00:11:56,965 --> 00:11:58,967
- You're doing it again, mia.
- What?

205
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:01,849
Blaming me for not giving you
what you need when you needed it.

206
00:12:01,974 --> 00:12:02,971
Now I get it

207
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:06,433
closure is you telling
me that it's all my fault

208
00:12:06,602 --> 00:12:08,202
and that I set you up.

209
00:12:08,710 --> 00:12:10,562
That way we can both
have what we want-

210
00:12:10,731 --> 00:12:13,565
I can be mad at you,
and you can be done with me.

211
00:12:13,733 --> 00:12:16,874
Here's where you tell me how relieved
I'll be when you walk out the door.

212
00:12:16,999 --> 00:12:19,527
And then you're going to say

213
00:12:19,761 --> 00:12:23,556
that you're like a knife in my neck,
that it'll feel good when you're gone.

214
00:12:23,681 --> 00:12:25,320
That how it goes, isn't it?

215
00:12:25,445 --> 00:12:27,339
See, this is your specialty, ia.

216
00:12:27,464 --> 00:12:30,469
And if you want to keep repeating
that pattern, that's fine. Go ahead.

217
00:12:30,594 --> 00:12:33,283
But if you want to make
a change in your life,

218
00:12:33,408 --> 00:12:35,938
I suggest that you stay in therapy.

219
00:12:37,111 --> 00:12:40,032
And it doesn't even
need to be with me.

220
00:12:41,889 --> 00:12:44,111
Can we talk about your patterns?

221
00:12:44,514 --> 00:12:45,614
My patterns?

222
00:12:46,641 --> 00:12:48,157
