254
00:14:41,089 --> 00:14:42,239
What if I do?

255
00:14:43,910 --> 00:14:45,185
What would happen?

256
00:14:45,310 --> 00:14:46,810
What are you saying?

257
00:14:47,887 --> 00:14:50,441
Would you finally
feel special enough?

258
00:14:51,422 --> 00:14:53,721
Would it fix everything,
to win like that?

259
00:14:53,846 --> 00:14:56,311
Or would you just blame
me for crossing the line?

260
00:14:56,479 --> 00:14:58,689
You're a lawyer, for chrissake.

261
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:01,900
You know what it would mean.

262
00:15:03,093 --> 00:15:05,843
Then I would be truly
guilty of malpractice.

263
00:15:06,377 --> 00:15:08,573
You've probably represented
doctors like that.

264
00:15:08,913 --> 00:15:11,963
Hell of a way to get out of therapy,
I have to say

265
00:15:12,126 --> 00:15:15,036
- turn me into one of your clients.
- That's not what I'm doing.

266
00:15:15,161 --> 00:15:17,332
Isn't it? Then I would need you.

267
00:15:17,896 --> 00:15:19,515
You would be in control.

268
00:15:19,640 --> 00:15:22,369
And that would be much
more comfortable for you,

269
00:15:22,494 --> 00:15:25,871
to have me back in your office.

270
00:15:32,060 --> 00:15:33,060
Maybe

271
00:15:38,032 --> 00:15:40,232
maybe that's why you really do it.

272
00:15:40,669 --> 00:15:41,522
What?

273
00:15:41,691 --> 00:15:43,817
- Your job.
- You're changing the topic.

274
00:15:43,985 --> 00:15:45,635
Are you getting scared?

275
00:15:50,421 --> 00:15:52,871
I'm trying to help you.
That's my job.

276
00:15:54,269 --> 00:15:57,664
What's yours, mia?
What do you do at work every day?

277
00:15:57,832 --> 00:16:00,232
You know as well
as anyone what I do.

278
00:16:03,541 --> 00:16:05,338
How is your case going?

279
00:16:05,506 --> 00:16:08,956
I wasn't in last week.
Don't you have a hearing coming up?

280
00:16:09,422 --> 00:16:11,152
So they tell me.

281
00:16:12,268 --> 00:16:14,968
But you're right, you
weren't in last week.

282
00:16:16,015 --> 00:16:19,811
If you had gone in, what cases
would you have been working on?

283
00:16:23,385 --> 00:16:25,922
No trials.
I was supposed to meet a new client

284
00:16:26,047 --> 00:16:27,736
a pediatrician who

285
00:16:28,057 --> 00:16:30,545
misdiagnosed some nine-year-old kid,

286
00:16:30,996 --> 00:16:32,297
almost killed him.

287
00:16:32,422 --> 00:16:34,322
No wonder you stayed in bed.

288
00:16:35,277 --> 00:16:37,535
I don't judge my clients, paul.

289
00:16:37,660 --> 00:16:38,830
I protect them.

290
00:16:39,258 --> 00:16:41,447
And how many of
your clients are powerful men

291
00:16:41,572 --> 00:16:44,051
who fail to protect
the vulnerable and the innocent?

292
00:16:44,176 --> 00:16:45,629
They're being sued, paul,

293
00:16:45,798 --> 00:16:48,298
just like you.
That doesn't mean they're guilty.

294
00:16:48,467 --> 00:16:50,258
And how long have
you been doing that?

295
00:16:52,441 --> 00:16:53,569
17 years.

296
00:16:53,795 --> 00:16:55,795
How often do you call in sick?

297
00:16:57,452 --> 00:16:58,852
Since I got there?

298
00:17:00,326 --> 00:17:01,626
Five days, four.

299
00:17:02,086 --> 00:17:03,449
In 17 years?

300
00:17:03,990 --> 00:17:05,190
And vacations?

301
00:17:07,031 --> 00:17:09,455
You don't lose the weeks
if you don't take them.

302
00:17:09,580 --> 00:17:11,279
I see. But last week,

303
00:17:11,447 --> 00:17:14,636
after confronting your father,
you didn't go in.

304
00:17:15,923 --> 00:17:17,806
According to you, I was depressed.

305
00:17:17,931 --> 00:17:19,086
I think you were.

306
00:17:19,211 --> 00:17:21,060
But I don't think it's a coincidence

307
00:17:21,185 --> 00:17:24,985
that suddenly you didn't want to
defend somebody whose negligence

308
00:17:25,152 --> 00:17:26,602
had harmed a child.

309
00:17:28,293 --> 00:17:30,471
Look, I'm not saying
they're all guilty,

310
00:17:30,596 --> 00:17:34,302
but every time you stand in
that courtroom to defend a client,

311
00:17:35,529 --> 00:17:39,029
I think you're actually defending
your father to everybody,

312
00:17:39,308 --> 00:17:40,808
especially yourself.

313
00:17:45,449 --> 00:17:46,449
Shit.

314
00:17:51,776 --> 00:17:53,613
How long have you known that one?

315
00:17:54,923 --> 00:17:56,723
Does it make sense to you?

316
00:18:03,114 --> 00:18:06,428
I never made the connexion...

317
00:18:07,151 --> 00:18:09,021
and now I'm stuck with it.

318
00:18:13,590 --> 00:18:17,290
I felt like I had nothing before.
Now I have less than nothing.

319
00:18:17,681 --> 00:18:19,835
I know it feels scary

320
00:18:20,178 --> 00:18:23,058
but maybe that's a good thing.

321
00:18:23,696 --> 00:18:26,146
It's a good thing
that I have nothing?

322
00:18:26,360 --> 00:18:27,434
Thank you.

323
00:18:28,391 --> 00:18:32,303
Thank you. You've helped me
to realize that I've made

324
00:18:32,870 --> 00:18:36,166
poor choice after poor choice
my whole life.

325
00:18:36,688 --> 00:18:39,458
But you also have to realize, Mia,

326
00:18:39,820 --> 00:18:42,786
that you're at a critical juncture
in your life,

327
00:18:43,231 --> 00:18:45,911
that now you do have
the self-knowledge

328
00:18:46,125 --> 00:18:48,133
to make different, better choices.

329
00:18:48,258 --> 00:18:50,950
Don't give me any of this
Pollyanna shit.

330
00:18:51,075 --> 00:18:53,166
And sometimes when you're
on the verge of real change,

331
00:18:53,291 --> 00:18:56,138
that's when you fight the hardest.

332
00:19:00,175 --> 00:19:02,040
When you first came back
I tried to ask you

333
00:19:02,165 --> 00:19:03,945
about your connection to your father

334
00:19:04,070 --> 00:19:06,497
and you shut me down. You didn't want
to know anything about it.

335
00:19:06,622 --> 00:19:09,773
This past week you confronted him.

336
00:19:10,020 --> 00:19:12,027
Yeah, look how well that worked out.

337
00:19:12,152 --> 00:19:15,649
I'm not saying it was easy.
But maybe it's worth it.

338
00:19:16,785 --> 00:19:19,778
To finally take off the blinders,

339
00:19:20,346 --> 00:19:23,717
even if you don't like what you see.
Because what is the alternative?

340
00:19:23,842 --> 00:19:27,242
Put them back on again
and wander around in the darkness?

341
00:19:28,476 --> 00:19:31,930
Did you have to take them off?
I didn't do it. You did.

342
00:19:35,666 --> 00:19:37,217
What are you thinking?

343
00:19:40,500 --> 00:19:41,889
Nothing.

344
00:19:43,661 --> 00:19:46,561
What am I going to do
with the rest of my life?

345
00:19:48,708 --> 00:19:49,720
I want...

346
00:19:50,096 --> 00:19:54,234
the same things I wanted
when I came here two months ago...

347
00:19:54,681 --> 00:19:57,995
a man, a home, a family.

348
00:19:59,783 --> 00:20:02,029
I'm no closer to getting them.

349
00:20:02,868 --> 00:20:07,149
Do you really think that getting married
is going to make it all better?

350
00:20:08,192 --> 00:20:11,216
Do you have any idea
of how many married people,

351
00:20:11,341 --> 00:20:15,324
how many parents feel
as empty as you do?

352
00:20:17,162 --> 00:20:18,550
Let me ask you...

353
00:20:18,836 --> 00:20:22,412
when was the last time
you felt real happiness?

354
00:20:24,505 --> 00:20:27,267
A couple weeks ago when I thought
that I was pregnant.

355
00:20:27,435 --> 00:20:29,991
And what about
that made you feel good?

356
00:20:30,663 --> 00:20:34,593
That it wasn't just me,
that my life had meaning,

357
00:20:36,882 --> 00:20:38,446
that there would be

358
00:20:39,503 --> 00:20:41,669
this other person, always.

359
00:20:43,131 --> 00:20:46,881
Have you ever considered that maybe
it's not about a child, Mia,

360
00:20:47,185 --> 00:20:48,943
or a husband?

361
00:20:50,500 --> 00:20:53,438
Maybe that's just a picture
in your head

362
00:20:53,563 --> 00:20:56,537
from your family, from your friends,

363
00:20:56,662 --> 00:20:58,725
from the culture.

364
00:20:59,401 --> 00:21:01,384
Not everyone needs that

365
00:21:01,751 --> 00:21:04,616
to live a full and contented life.

366
00:21:07,152 --> 00:21:11,120
Maybe what you really want, Mia,
is to feel connected,

367
00:21:11,855 --> 00:21:13,612
authentically connected

368
00:21:14,748 --> 00:21:17,222
to somebody or something else.

369
00:21:17,611 --> 00:21:19,899
And we both know
that I can't have that.

370
00:21:20,024 --> 00:21:22,771
- Why not?
- An authentic connection? Me?

371
00:21:22,896 --> 00:21:26,696
- I've never had that. I'm incapable.
- Are you sure?

372
00:21:26,821 --> 00:21:28,601
What about in here?

373
00:21:29,320 --> 00:21:31,257
Are you kidding me?

374
00:21:31,821 --> 00:21:33,682
I'm a mess in here.

375
00:21:34,023 --> 00:21:37,684
I attack you. I've dumped on you.
I've tried to seduce you.

376
00:21:37,809 --> 00:21:41,632
- I've been a train wreck.
- Okay, at times you have acted out.

377
00:21:41,801 --> 00:21:44,907
But if you hadn't,
how could we examine it?

378
00:21:45,894 --> 00:21:49,656
It's been your way of communicating
to both of us what you need.

379
00:21:50,961 --> 00:21:52,477
You've also been honest,

380
00:21:52,752 --> 00:21:55,302
caring.
You've made yourself vulnerable.

381
00:21:56,914 --> 00:21:59,831
You've shown me who you really are.

382
00:22:00,280 --> 00:22:02,180
And you haven't walked away.

383
00:22:03,997 --> 00:22:04,989
Yet.

384
00:22:05,579 --> 00:22:08,409
We both know
that you really want to change.

385
00:22:09,448 --> 00:22:11,955
That's the real reason
you keep coming back.

386
00:22:12,699 --> 00:22:15,416
Yes, of course you want
intimacy in your life.

387
00:22:15,541 --> 00:22:16,584
And I know...

388
00:22:17,627 --> 00:22:20,105
I know that you're capable of that.

389
00:22:20,950 --> 00:22:24,496
- Because we've had it.
- When? Name one time.

390
00:22:24,976 --> 00:22:26,627
Now.
Right now.

391
00:23:01,623 --> 00:23:02,880
Our time is up, right?

392
00:23:09,259 --> 00:23:10,559
Thank you, Paul.

393
00:23:15,947 --> 00:23:17,353
It was a good session.

394
00:23:30,339 --> 00:23:31,489
Goodbye, Mia.

395
00:23:35,148 --> 00:23:36,148
So...

396
00:23:39,496 --> 00:23:41,546
I guess I'll see you next week.

397
00:23:46,417 --> 00:23:47,666
I'll be here.

